[00:00.00] Michelangelo lay on the scaffold high
[00:10.00] With paint in his beard and dust in his eye
[00:20.00] He chipped at the marble to find the vein
[00:30.00] He bargained with God through the physical pain
[00:40.00] But I sit slouched in an ergonomic chair
[00:50.00] Blue light bathing my thinning hair
[01:00.00] No callus on finger, no stain on the smock
[01:10.00] Just waiting for the render... watching the clock
[01:20.00] This is the Sistine Simulation
[01:30.00] A cathedral built on calculation
[01:40.00] I reach out my hand to the Adam I made
[01:50.00] But the image dissolves, and the pixels fade
[02:00.00] There is no spark, no divine ignition
[02:10.00] Just a hollow, high-res apparition
[02:20.00] I asked for the beauty of sixteen-twelve
[02:30.00] I told the machine to deeply delve
[02:40.00] It gave me the colors, the shadow, the light
[02:50.00] But something within it is not quite right
[03:05.00] Look at the fingers, look at the skin
[03:15.00] The eyes are too empty, the mouth is too thin
[03:25.00] I summoned a David from noise and from static
[03:35.00] But he has no soul... only mathematics
[03:45.00] I am not a creator. I am a requester
[03:55.00] I am a tourist in the gallery of my own imagination
[04:05.00] I type "Style of Da Vinci"
[04:15.00] And I steal the ghost of a dead man's hand
[04:25.00] To paint a world I do not understand
[04:35.00] This is the Sistine Simulation
[04:45.00] A cathedral built on calculation
[04:55.00] I reach out my hand to the Adam I made
[05:05.00] But the image dissolves, and the pixels fade
[05:15.00] There is no spark, no divine ignition
[05:25.00] Just a hollow, high-res apparition
[05:35.00] The fingers... They never touch
[05:45.00] They never touch. Glitch
